        </p>
        <p class="lead">In June, an official agreement is signed between the government, Losirwa and Mungere community members and Red Sweater Project to build the area’s first middle and high school, serving over 5,000 community members. The village donates 15 acres of land on which to build the Mungere Secondary School, stewarding the school’s success by participating in construction and operations.
